17/06/2004
BELGRADE, Serbia-Montenegro -- B92 reported Thursday (17 June) that Prime Minister Vojislav Kostunica's Democratic Party of Serbia has decided to publicly support Boris Tadic in the 27 June presidential run-off. 
Tadic, of the Democratic Party, faces ultranationalist Tomislav Nikolic. 
G17 Plus, another ruling coalition party, has already backed Tadic, whose party is currently excluded from the government. 
(B92 - 17/06/04; Tanjug, B92 - 16/06/04)
